This approach works for rules that can find frequent positive examples.
The challenge arises for rules that need to govern entities and facts that are rare, and for negative rules that need to prohibit some facts from appearing.
To handle these cases, contextual information can be exploited. In this context, LLMs bring a number of important opportunities: